<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>The personal website of Jon Saville</title><link>https://jonsaville.com/</link><description>Recent content on The personal website of Jon Saville</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Thu, 01 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://jonsaville.com/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Happy New Year 2026</title><link>https://jonsaville.com/post/2026/01/happy-new-year-2026/</link><pubDate>Thu, 01 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://jonsaville.com/post/2026/01/happy-new-year-2026/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;2025 was a busy and challenging year (the only kind these days it seems). On the personal front, I managed to stick to a couple of last year&amp;rsquo;s resolutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I have always found it difficult to keeping to a daily regime. I get absorbed in some problem, and it&amp;rsquo;s suddenly the next day. But I managed to make a short diary entry every day in 2025, thanks to a basic template in the &lt;a href="https://dayoneapp.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Day One&lt;/a&gt; app, and I wish I&amp;rsquo;d started this years ago.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I was a voracious reader of science fiction as a teenager, but as an adult my reading dropped off in favour of other distractions. I&amp;rsquo;ve been trying to get back it for a while, but 2025 was the first year where it stuck - partly by limiting time on social media, and partly by bootstrapping the habit on a series of very readable novels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I finished 28 books in 2025: 13 in the science fiction genre, 10 urban fantasy and 5 general fiction.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Happy New Year 2025</title><link>https://jonsaville.com/post/2025/01/happy-new-year-2025/</link><pubDate>Wed, 01 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://jonsaville.com/post/2025/01/happy-new-year-2025/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Another year, another post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2024 was a big year for my family - my sister got married, my parents downsized from the house I grew up in, and I turned 50 during a holiday in the Scottish Highlands. That holiday coincided with the solar storm in May, and we were treated to a spectacular aurora display in spectacular surroundings. 2025 promises to be just as busy.&lt;/p&gt;






































































