&lt;p&gt;This was an experiment to decode the SPI data sent from a Pico to a &lt;a href="https://shop.pimoroni.com/products/pico-display-pack" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;TFT display&lt;/a&gt; from Pimoroni, using my &lt;a href="https://jonsaville.com/post/2021/02/new-test-gear/"&gt;recent purchase&lt;/a&gt; - the Siglent SDS1104X-E oscilloscope.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To generate some test data, I modified the sample program supplied with the display to place four blocks of colour in the corners. These colour blocks are rotated every 10 seconds.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>New test gear: Oscilloscope and signal generator</title><link>https://jonsaville.com/post/2021/02/new-test-gear/</link><pubDate>Sat, 20 Feb 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://jonsaville.com/post/2021/02/new-test-gear/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;I finally gave in and bought an oscilloscope, the &lt;a href="https://www.siglenteu.com/digital-oscilloscopes/sds1000x-e-series-super-phosphor-oscilloscopes/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Siglent SDS1104X-E&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;






































































